itively on $M_{\\rm H}$,\nwith the trapping cycle and trapping amplitude larger for thinner H envelopes.\nAlso, the asymptotic period spacing is longer for thinner H envelopes. Finally,\nwe found asteroseismological models (when possible) characterized by canonical\n(thick) and by thin H envelope, with $T_{\\rm eff}$ and $M_*$ in agreement with\nthe spectroscopic determinations. The fact that we have found\nasteroseismological solutions with H envelopes thinner than canonical gives a\nclue of the possible scenario of formation of these stars. Indeed, in the light\nof our results, some of these stars could have been formed by binary evolution\nthrough unstable mass loss.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Fri, 26 Oct 2018 18:52:39 GMT"}],"update_date":"2018-12-19"}
